07:37.916 --> 07:40.502
Ooh.

07:40.585 --> 07:41.628
Sorry!

07:44.839 --> 07:46.007
[NPR meteorologist]
<i>Now going into the fifth week</i>

07:46.091 --> 07:48.802
<i>of this record‐breaking
heat wave, local officials are</i>

07:48.885 --> 07:51.179
<i>closely monitoring all areas
affected by the drought.</i>

07:51.262 --> 07:53.640
<i>With reservoirs
at an all‐time low...</i>

07:59.229 --> 08:00.730
Are you Helen Butler?

08:01.940 --> 08:03.858
I am. Can I help you?

08:03.942 --> 08:05.360
My name's Mariel Rodriguez.

08:05.443 --> 08:06.361
I'm a social worker
from the Los Angeles Department

08:06.444 --> 08:08.697
of Children and Family Services.

08:08.780 --> 08:11.116
I'd like to ask you some
questions about your neighbor,

08:11.199 --> 08:13.702
‐Sierra James.
‐Is Sierra okay?

08:13.785 --> 08:14.536
It's standard procedure

08:14.619 --> 08:16.871
to speak with friends
and neighbors

08:16.955 --> 08:17.747
of the subject
of an open investigation.

08:20.583 --> 08:22.544
Okay. Do we need
to go inside, or...?

08:22.627 --> 08:24.129
This won't take that long.

08:24.212 --> 08:25.547
When was the last time
you saw Ms. James

08:25.630 --> 08:27.716
with her child,
and how did they appear?

08:27.799 --> 08:28.717
Mm, I‐I haven't seen them

08:28.800 --> 08:31.094
for a couple weeks,
but she seemed... fine.

08:31.177 --> 08:33.888
Can you be more specific?

08:33.972 --> 08:36.140
A little tired, maybe,
but she's a new mother.

08:36.224 --> 08:37.726
That's to be expected.

08:37.808 --> 08:39.686
Anything else?
Aberrant behavior?

08:39.769 --> 08:42.105
Drugs and alcohol?
Poor decision‐making?

08:42.188 --> 08:44.524
Nope. Just tired.

08:47.318 --> 08:48.737
Uh, can I ask what
she's being investigated for?

08:48.820 --> 08:52.866
I'm not at liberty to say.
Thank you for your time.

08:54.075 --> 08:55.452
‐[knocking]
‐[meditative music playing]

08:55.535 --> 08:57.495
Sierra?

08:57.579 --> 08:58.705
[Eddie crying]

09:04.044 --> 09:06.504
Sierra?

09:06.588 --> 09:08.506
[Eddie crying]

09:08.590 --> 09:10.717
Sierra, what is going on?
Where's Eddie?

09:10.800 --> 09:12.385
‐He's... upstairs.
‐[music shuts off]

09:12.469 --> 09:14.763
I'm letting him cry it out.

09:14.846 --> 09:17.599
That's for nighttime,
not the middle of the day.

09:17.682 --> 09:19.350
I'm just really stressed
out right now, okay?

09:19.434 --> 09:23.271
Oh. Okay. Well, are you aware

09:23.354 --> 09:25.774
you're being investigated
by Child Protective Services?

09:25.857 --> 09:28.568
It's not a big deal.
I got into

09:28.651 --> 09:29.527
a minor accident
a couple weeks back.

09:29.611 --> 09:32.739
Nobody was hurt.
Just, I hit a dumpster.

09:32.822 --> 09:35.283
But why are social services
investigating a car accident?

09:35.366 --> 09:37.577
Because the car was totaled.

09:37.660 --> 09:39.162
And Eddie was in it.

09:39.245 --> 09:41.247
Sierra, this is... serious.

09:41.331 --> 09:42.123
You could lose him!

09:42.207 --> 09:44.417
I know.

09:44.501 --> 09:45.794
I'm handling it.

09:45.877 --> 09:47.045
Okay. Yeah.

09:47.128 --> 09:48.254
[scoffs]

09:48.338 --> 09:51.257
Look, I have to go pick up
Stacey and Trevor, but you need

09:51.341 --> 09:53.468
to get up and get dressed
and clean the fucking house.

09:53.551 --> 09:57.639
Okay? You are not the first
woman on Earth to have a child.

09:57.722 --> 09:59.516
You need to grow up
and figure out how

09:59.599 --> 10:00.100
to take care of that baby!

10:00.183 --> 10:01.559
[Eddie wailing]

10:01.643 --> 10:02.977
Since when do you care
about him?

10:03.061 --> 10:05.230
I... What?

10:05.313 --> 10:06.815
The night that
I crashed the car,

10:06.898 --> 10:08.483
I came over to your house,
and I asked you for help.

10:08.566 --> 10:10.819
You said you were too busy.

10:10.902 --> 10:12.028
[Eddie wailing]

10:12.112 --> 10:15.031
And now, suddenly, you care
about what happens to us?

10:15.115 --> 10:16.491
Please.

10:16.574 --> 10:18.034
Can I have my weed back?

10:18.118 --> 10:21.371
<i>♪ gentle music ♪</i>

10:21.454 --> 10:22.247
<i>♪♪♪</i>

10:22.330 --> 10:25.166
[Eddie wailing]

10:25.250 --> 10:27.252
How about you get
the fuck off the couch

10:27.335 --> 10:29.212
and go comfort your kid?

10:29.295 --> 10:31.464
[Eddie continues crying]

10:34.175 --> 10:36.344
[phone buzzes]

10:36.427 --> 10:38.513
<i>♪♪♪</i>

10:49.107 --> 10:50.024
[indistinct chatter]

10:50.108 --> 10:52.986
<i>♪♪♪</i>

11:02.370 --> 11:05.290
‐Sure.
‐[phone chimes]

11:18.803 --> 11:20.930
[Christianna]
Thanks for coming all this way.

11:21.806 --> 11:23.057
I hope you like iced lattes.

11:23.141 --> 11:25.185
Thank you.

11:25.268 --> 11:27.520
I am so sorry for
the cryptic messages. I just...

11:27.604 --> 11:30.064
I really needed
to talk to you.

11:30.148 --> 11:31.232
Look, I could just tell

11:31.316 --> 11:33.568
that you're not like all
of Sasha's other girlfriends.

11:33.651 --> 11:35.695
You're like a real
human being.

11:35.778 --> 11:37.280
You're not just trying
to get close to him

11:37.363 --> 11:40.450
because he's famous.

11:40.533 --> 11:45.079
And I can tell he's really crazy
about you, so...

11:45.163 --> 11:47.373
Has he told you
about my mother at all?

11:47.457 --> 11:49.042
Um, a little. Yeah.

11:49.125 --> 11:51.878
He told you
she was an addict, right?

11:51.961 --> 11:56.090
Has he told you that
he's the one who got her hooked?

11:58.218 --> 12:01.095
No.

12:01.179 --> 12:04.724
Or how about the fact
that she was the one

12:04.807 --> 12:07.435
who supported the two of them
for an entire decade

12:07.518 --> 12:09.020
at the beginning of his career?

12:09.103 --> 12:10.605
Did he tell you that?

12:10.688 --> 12:11.856
No, um, I don't know,
but I'm sorry. I didn't...

12:11.940 --> 12:13.983
What‐what does this have
to do with me exactly?

12:16.110 --> 12:18.154
She left me money.

12:18.238 --> 12:20.156
My grandparents were rich,

12:20.240 --> 12:22.659
and Sasha's in charge of it.

12:22.742 --> 12:24.953
He's supposed
to pay me an income every year,

12:25.036 --> 12:26.371
but he never does.

12:26.454 --> 12:27.789
I mean, I have
to practically squat

12:27.872 --> 12:28.957
at his house
to get him to pay me.

12:29.040 --> 12:32.710
That money that you were
asking for is your money?

12:33.878 --> 12:35.338
Well, why would he do that?

12:35.421 --> 12:37.382
I had a bad couple of years.

12:37.465 --> 12:39.300
I fucked up a bit.

12:39.384 --> 12:41.761
I... tried committing suicide.

12:41.844 --> 12:44.055
I mean, my mom had just died,
for fuck's sake.

12:44.138 --> 12:46.641
But all of that
is behind me now.

12:46.724 --> 12:48.101
I have

12:48.184 --> 12:49.811
an apartment, I have two jobs.

12:49.894 --> 12:51.312
I'm writing a book.

12:51.396 --> 12:53.273
That's great.
I mean, it sounds

12:53.356 --> 12:55.358
‐really great.
