But she fired him.

51:42.224 --> 51:43.726
Oh, God.
[exhales]

51:43.809 --> 51:45.477
All right.

51:45.561 --> 51:47.313
I'll set up a call
for all of us tomorrow.

51:47.396 --> 51:51.275
We'll discuss next steps
in case the worst happens.

51:51.358 --> 51:51.984
In the meantime, go home.

51:52.067 --> 51:53.736
Cancel all public appearances.

51:53.819 --> 51:56.113
And, for crying out loud,

51:56.196 --> 51:58.490
keep your hands to yourself.

51:58.574 --> 52:00.451
And circle your wagons.

52:00.534 --> 52:02.703
Meaning what?

52:03.203 --> 52:06.248
Tell your family.

52:07.750 --> 52:09.877
<i>[jazz playing]</i>

52:10.836 --> 52:12.671
[sighs]

52:13.672 --> 52:16.175
[woman over P. A.]
<i>Flight 117 to Tel Aviv</i>

52:16.258 --> 52:19.595
<i>will now be departing
from Gate 45.</i>

52:19.678 --> 52:23.474
<i>Flight 117 to Tel Aviv will
now be departing from Gate 45.</i>

52:29.021 --> 52:31.982
[quietly]
Fuck, that's tonight.

52:38.322 --> 52:41.241
[woman over P. A.]
<i>Good afternoon, passengers.</i>

52:41.325 --> 52:43.619
<i>This is a pre‐boarding
announcement for Flight 1537</i>

52:43.702 --> 52:46.372
<i>to Los Angeles.</i>

52:46.455 --> 52:49.833
<i>We are now inviting those
passengers with small children</i>

52:49.917 --> 52:51.877
<i>and passengers requiring
special assistance</i>

52:51.960 --> 52:55.047
<i>to begin boarding at this time.</i>

52:55.130 --> 52:58.175
<i>Please have your boarding pass
and identification ready.</i>

52:58.258 --> 53:00.219
<i>Regular boarding
will begin in ten minutes.</i>

53:00.302 --> 53:02.179
<i>Thank you.</i>

53:02.262 --> 53:04.848
<i>♪ ominous piano music ♪</i>

53:04.932 --> 53:07.017
<i>♪♪♪</i>

53:21.490 --> 53:23.367
[indistinct chatter]

53:26.954 --> 53:30.416
[MC] ...of the Art Seidenbaum
Award for First Fiction,

53:30.499 --> 53:32.918
Armando Solis.

53:33.001 --> 53:35.087
[applause]

53:36.338 --> 53:39.091
[Armando] Thank you.
Thank you, <i>L. A. Times.</i>

53:39.174 --> 53:42.928
English wasn't
my first language,

53:43.011 --> 53:45.097
but it was the language
I chose to...

53:45.180 --> 53:48.434
give voice to this first piece
of fiction,

53:48.517 --> 53:49.852
this first
declaration

53:49.935 --> 53:50.936
of self.

53:51.019 --> 53:52.104
And I think
it was the only choice,

53:52.187 --> 53:53.480
because English

53:53.564 --> 53:54.606
makes no sense.

53:54.690 --> 53:55.441
I‐In a wonderful way.

53:55.524 --> 53:58.819
Really. It has
less of a road map,

53:58.902 --> 53:59.695
less...

53:59.778 --> 54:00.904
internal logic.

54:00.988 --> 54:03.824
[continues indistinctly]

54:16.587 --> 54:18.922
<i>♪♪♪</i>

54:23.844 --> 54:25.929
[applause]

54:27.806 --> 54:29.641
Eden,

54:29.725 --> 54:30.225
I just want to talk to you.

54:30.309 --> 54:32.519
Noah,
I'm a publicist,

54:32.603 --> 54:33.729
and I'm gonna give you some
professional advice for free.

54:33.812 --> 54:36.398
Walk away.

54:36.482 --> 54:37.733
Right now.

54:37.816 --> 54:39.818
Did you say all those things
about me to Petra?

54:39.902 --> 54:42.571
I talked to Petra, yes.

54:42.654 --> 54:45.616
Okay, now, I have
a very different memory

54:45.699 --> 54:48.827
of what happened
between us that night.

54:48.911 --> 54:49.912
Uh, we‐we were friends,
weren't we?

54:49.995 --> 54:52.456
We‐we were having fun.

54:52.539 --> 54:54.416
‐I worked for you.
‐But‐‐

54:54.500 --> 54:56.835
It was my job
to keep you happy.

54:56.919 --> 54:59.588
Even as your demands got
more and more ridiculous.

54:59.671 --> 55:00.339
What demands?

55:00.422 --> 55:03.050
That I come to your hotel room.

55:03.133 --> 55:04.343
When you were drunk.

55:04.426 --> 55:06.929
Oh, come on.
Eden, that's not what happened.

55:07.012 --> 55:09.181
That I do drugs
with you.

55:10.933 --> 55:12.017
[quietly]
That I have sex with you.

55:12.100 --> 55:14.520
Eden, that was your idea.

55:14.603 --> 55:15.521
‐[stammering]
‐[scoffs]

55:15.604 --> 55:16.522
At Rodney's party?

55:16.605 --> 55:17.940
I was just trying
to get home to my wife!

55:18.023 --> 55:18.774
Oh, my God.

55:18.857 --> 55:20.567
At least be honest
with yourself.

55:20.651 --> 55:22.069
No, you be honest with yourself.
You remember...

55:22.152 --> 55:23.237
you remember how you
were dressed that night?

55:23.320 --> 55:25.364
You remember
how you were dancing with me?

55:25.447 --> 55:26.865
You were coming on to me.

55:26.949 --> 55:28.784
Excuse me.
I've got to get back to my job.

55:28.867 --> 55:31.495
No, Eden.

55:32.955 --> 55:34.706
You wanted
to fuck me,

55:34.790 --> 55:36.458
and I walked away.

55:36.542 --> 55:38.835
Now, I don't know if that
pissed you off, and this is

55:38.919 --> 55:40.712
some kind of sick revenge.
But I have a family.

55:40.796 --> 55:42.548
I have two daughters.

55:42.631 --> 55:44.258
And you're gonna ruin my life.

55:44.341 --> 55:46.343
So, please, this is not a game.

55:46.426 --> 55:47.886
<i>♪ dramatic, tense music ♪</i>

55:47.970 --> 55:52.182
<i>♪♪♪</i>

55:52.266 --> 55:53.892
I'm not afraid
of you anymore, Noah.

55:53.976 --> 55:56.937
Afraid of me?

55:57.020 --> 55:59.481
I didn't go looking
for this moment.

55:59.565 --> 56:01.567
A reporter called me, and...

56:01.650 --> 56:03.735
I decided to tell the truth.

56:03.819 --> 56:05.112
She called you? Why?

56:05.195 --> 56:08.115
Noah, I'm doing you a favor.

56:08.198 --> 56:10.075
I won't tell anybody
you stalked me here.

56:10.158 --> 56:11.285
But you need to leave now.

56:11.368 --> 56:15.872
Or everyone's gonna know
about this.

56:15.956 --> 56:17.749
[indistinct chatter]

56:17.833 --> 56:20.210
<i>♪♪♪</i>

56:20.294 --> 56:21.253
Seriously.

56:21.336 --> 56:23.547
[crowd murmuring]

56:25.924 --> 56:28.802
[siren wailing]

56:31.680 --> 56:33.849
[horn honking]

56:33.932 --> 56:36.018
<i>♪♪♪</i>

56:42.649 --> 56:44.401
Hi.

56:44.484 --> 56:46.695
‐Hi.
‐What a nice surprise.

56:46.778 --> 56:48.238
I thought
you were still in Montauk.

56:48.322 --> 56:50.365
No, I‐I just got home.

56:50.449 --> 56:52.117
I just came by to...

56:52.200 --> 56:54.161
wish you a happy birthday.

56:54.244 --> 56:55.621
I brought dinner.

56:55.704 --> 56:57.789
‐I don't know if you guys have‐‐
‐Oh, that's so sweet.

56:57.873 --> 56:59.291
I mean, we ate already,
but the kids made cake.

56:59.374 --> 56:59.958
Do you want to come in?

57:00.042 --> 57:02.836
Sure.

57:05.213 --> 57:06.798
[Stacey]
Dad!

57:06.882 --> 57:08.133
Hey. Hey, Stacey.

57:08.216 --> 57:11.178
<i>[music playing faintly]</i>

57:11.261 --> 57:12.095
Perfect timing.
We were just about

57:12.179 --> 57:14.306
to sing "Happy Birthday."

57:14.389 --> 57:16.642
[chuckles]
Great.

57:16.725 --> 57:18.226
‐Hey, Dad.
‐Hey, Trev.

57:18.310 --> 57:19.811
Nice cake.

57:19.895 --> 57:21.563
Thank you.

57:23.190 --> 57:26.151
Lasagna for my birthday.

57:26.234 --> 57:26.610
Thank you.

57:28.737 --> 57:30.489
How's Whitney?

57:30.572 --> 57:31.448
Uh, she's good.
She's‐she's great.

57:31.531 --> 57:34.034
[Helen] Thank you again
for doing that.

57:34.117 --> 57:35.661
No, no. It was my pleasure.

57:35.744 --> 57:38.038
And Martin called today.

57:38.121 --> 57:40.248
He says he made
the dean's list.

57:40.332 --> 57:42.209
‐You're kidding me.
‐Nope.

57:42.292 --> 57:45.003
[exhales]
We did good, Solloway, somehow.

57:47.089 --> 57:49.007
Uh, do you want some?

57:49.091 --> 57:50.258
The kids and I
are about to have a toast.

57:50.342 --> 57:52.052
What, even Stacey?

57:52.135 --> 57:53.595
‐She can have a little.
‐[phone ringing]

57:53.679 --> 57:54.596
Sure.

57:58.475 --> 58:00.185
That's so weird.
This New York number

58:00.268 --> 58:02.729
has been calling me all day, and
they won't leave a voice mail.

58:02.813 --> 58:03.480
Hello.

58:03.563 --> 58:07.025
Yeah, this is Helen Solloway.

58:07.109 --> 58:10.278
I'm sorry,
from what magazine?

58:10.362 --> 58:13.031
[quietly]
<i>Vanity Fair.</i>

58:13.115 --> 58:14.491
‐Helen‐‐
‐Uh, okay. I need two minutes.

58:14.574 --> 58:16.660
Can we start drinking
without you?

58:16.743 --> 58:18.870
[whispers]
It's just two minutes.

58:18.954 --> 58:20.038
‐Helen‐‐
‐Okay, Petra,

58:20.122 --> 58:22.040
what can I do for you?

58:22.124 --> 58:23.875
<i>♪ dramatic, tense music ♪</i>

58:23.959 --> 58:26.878
[balloon inflating]

58:36.555 --> 58:38.557
<i>♪ atmospheric music ♪</i>

